# Hard Keys HTML versioning

Applies to **`Assets/Hard Keys/**/*.html`** and mirrored runtime templates under **`src/sentinel/ui/testing/hard_keys/*.html`**.

## Rule

**Each revision that changes layout, spacing, CSS geometry, DOM structure, `data-label`s, or other meaningful behavior must ship under a new version.** Do not ship substantive edits under an unchanged version string.

## Versioned filenames (`*Template*v*.html`, e.g. ISR-2 / ISR-4 / T4x Template)

1. **Bump the integer in the filename** for that edit: copy to the next version (`v2` → `v3`, etc.). Keep the prior file in the repo as history unless the user asks to delete it.
2. **Update in-file metadata** to match: `<title>`, top HTML comments, `aria-label` (and any other strings that name the version).
3. **Do not** add, edit, or sync copies under **`Assets/Hard Keys/Usable Templates/`** unless the user explicitly asks—canonical files live only in **`Assets/Hard Keys/`** (plus `src/.../hard_keys/` for runtime).

## Canonical layout HTML (fixed names, e.g. `T4x Hard Keys.html`, `ISR-4 Hard Keys.html`)

The filename may stay stable. Still **increment the documented version** every revision:

- `<title>` (e.g. `T4x Hard Keys v3`)
- A short **`<!-- vN: … -->`** comment after `<head>` (or equivalent) summarizing what changed vs `vN-1`
- Root **`aria-label`** on `.frame` / `.chrome` when it names the version

## Runtime mirrors (`src/sentinel/ui/testing/hard_keys/*.html`)

When the Assets canonical file changes, sync content per **`registry.py`** / project practice and **match the same version comment/title/aria** so `src/` never looks older than Assets.

## Waivers

Only **trivial, non-layout** edits (typo in comment, whitespace, no geometry/DOM change) may skip a version bump—and only when the user explicitly allows it.
